# Patch 0009 — Workspace archiving (Kavacha platform plan — workspaces as
# persistent projects).
#
# What: "Archive Space" (space actions menu or palette) hides a space from
# the strip, icon row, switch menus and scroll/shortcut navigation, and
# unloads its tabs to free memory — while keeping ALL its data: tabs stay in
# the session store, the space keeps syncing, notes and identity settings
# are untouched. "Archived Spaces" submenu restores one instantly (restore
# switches to it). Archiving the active space switches to the next visible
# space first; the last visible space cannot be archived. Element hiding is
# re-applied at every switch, which also covers startup restore.
# Deliberately NOT filtered in getWorkspaces() itself: that feeds the
# session store and sync — archived spaces must persist. Filtering happens
# at the UI/navigation call sites only.
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceIcons.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl,
#          src/zen/urlbar/ZenUBGlobalActions.sys.mjs,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl.
# Applies on top of 0008.
